Switch or Case Statement
------------------------
instead of nested if statement we can use switch case statement.
to check the variable value against the cases.

Example
--------
-Create Java Project
-Create class 
-Create the body of the main.

int number = 12;

switch(number){
case 1: System.out.println("Number 1"); break;
case 2: System.out.println("Number 2"); break;
case 4: System.out.println("Number 3"); break;
case 5: System.out.println("Number 4"); break;
case 6: System.out.println("Number 5"); break;
default:System.out.println("The default case); break;
}
